<paragraph id="8BC636FD2F25A254FF73FDE56852FDFD" blockId="2.[151,1113,588,610]" box="[151,1113,588,610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FEC2FDE46F55FDFD" authority="Trouessart, 1885" authorityName="Trouessart" authorityYear="1885" box="[294,862,588,610]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Proctophyllodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis" subGenus="Pterodectes">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FEC2FDE46DC0FDFD" box="[294,459,588,610]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Proctophyllodes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FE3EFDE46E5BFDFD" box="[474,592,588,610]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Pterodectes</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FDBBFDE46EA7FDFD" box="[607,684,588,610]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">gracilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FD57FDE56F55FDFD" author="Trouessart" box="[691,862,588,610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Trouessart, E. L. (1885) Note sur la classification des Analgesiens et diagnoses d'especes et de genres nouveaux. Bulletin de la Societe d'Etudes Scientifiques d'Angers, 14, 46 - 89." type="journal article" year="1885">Trouessart, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC636FD2F25A254FF73FD226E23FA99" blockId="2.[151,1437,649,1394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
Among the 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FECDFD216DA7FD3D" box="[297,428,649,674]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Pterodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FECDFD216DA7FD3D" box="[297,428,649,674]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Pterodectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
generic complex, which currently includes seven genera (
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FB96FD216993FD3D" authority="Robin, 1877" authorityName="Robin" authorityYear="1877" box="[1138,1432,649,674]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Pterodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FB96FD2168FEFD3D" box="[1138,1269,649,674]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Pterodectes</emphasis>
Robin, 1877
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FF73FD056E76FD59" authority="Valim &amp; Hernandes, 2010" authorityName="Valim &amp; Hernandes" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,637,685,710]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Amerodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FF73FD056D2CFD59" box="[151,295,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Amerodectes</emphasis>
Valim &amp; Hernandes, 2010
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FD76FD056F1DFD59" box="[658,790,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Berladectes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FCC3FD056867FD59" author="Valim" box="[807,1132,685,710]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Valim, M. P. &amp; Hernandes, F. A. (2008) Redescription of five species of the feather mite genus Pterodectes Robin, 1877 (Acari: Proctophyllodidae: Pterodectinae), with the proposal of a new genus and a new species. Acarina, 16, 131 - 158." type="journal article" year="2008">Valim &amp; Hernandes, 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FB65FD056D6EFD75" authority="Valim &amp; Hernandes, 2008" authorityName="Valim &amp; Hernandes" authorityYear="2008" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Cotingodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FB65FD05692AFD59" box="[1153,1313,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Cotingodectes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FAD6FD056D6EFD75" author="Valim" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Valim, M. P. &amp; Hernandes, F. A. (2008) Redescription of five species of the feather mite genus Pterodectes Robin, 1877 (Acari: Proctophyllodidae: Pterodectinae), with the proposal of a new genus and a new species. Acarina, 16, 131 - 158." type="journal article" year="2008">Valim &amp; Hernandes, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FE99FD796F09FD75" authority="Mironov, 2008" authorityName="Mironov" authorityYear="2008" box="[381,770,721,746]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Metapterodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FE99FD796E3CFD75" box="[381,567,721,746]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Metapterodectes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FDA8FD796F09FD75" author="Mironov" box="[588,770,721,746]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V., Literak, I. &amp; Capek, M. (2008) New feather mites of the subfamily Pterodectinae (Acari: Astigmata: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) in Mato Grosso do Sul, Brazil. Zootaxa, 1947, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2008">Mironov, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FCFFFD796889FD75" authority="Mironov, 2008" authorityName="Mironov" authorityYear="2008" box="[795,1154,721,746]" class="Aves" family="Furnariidae" genus="Tyrannidectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FCFFFD796FB3FD75" box="[795,952,721,746]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Tyrannidectes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FC28FD796889FD75" author="Mironov" box="[972,1154,721,746]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V., Literak, I. &amp; Capek, M. (2008) New feather mites of the subfamily Pterodectinae (Acari: Astigmata: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) in Mato Grosso do Sul, Brazil. Zootaxa, 1947, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2008">Mironov, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FB3CFD796997FD75" box="[1240,1436,721,746]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Hemitriccodectes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FF73FD5D6D52FC91" author="Hernandes" box="[151,345,757,782]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Hernandes, F. A. (2013) A new genus and species of pterodectine feather mite (Acari: Proctophyllodidae) from Tody-Tyrants in Brazil (Passeriformes: Tyrannidae). Acta Parasitologica, 58, 309 - 316. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2478 / s 11686 - 013 - 0153 - 7" type="journal article" year="2013">Hernandes, 2013</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FE8AFD5D6DF6FC91" box="[366,509,757,782]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Amerodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FE8AFD5D6DF6FC91" box="[366,509,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Amerodectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most species-rich genus, currently comprising 28 species including the two species described below (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FE20FCB26E89FCAD" author="Trouessart" box="[452,642,793,818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Trouessart, E. L. (1885) Note sur la classification des Analgesiens et diagnoses d'especes et de genres nouveaux. Bulletin de la Societe d'Etudes Scientifiques d'Angers, 14, 46 - 89." type="journal article" year="1885">Trouessart 1885</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FD70FCB16F04FCAD" author="Stoll" box="[660,783,793,818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Stoll, O. (1893) Arachnida Acaridea. Biologia Centrali-Americana, Zoology, 3, 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="1893">Stoll 1893</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FCC4FCB16FAFFCAD" author="Berla" box="[800,932,793,818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Berla, H. F. (1958) Analgesidae Neotropicais. I-Duas novas especies de Pterodectes Robin, 1868 (Acarina- Proctophyllodinae) coletadas em Fringillidae, Aves, Passeriformes. Boletim do Museu Nacional (Zoologia), 209, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="1958">Berla 1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FC51FCB26FFBFCAD" author="Berla" box="[949,1008,794,818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Berla, H. F. (1973) Analgesoidea Neotropicais. X-Uma nova especie de Pterodectes Robin, 1877. Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 33 (1), 21 - 22." type="journal article" year="1973">1973</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FBE5FCB16885FCAD" author="Cerny" box="[1025,1166,793,818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Cerny, V. (1974) Parasitic mites of Surinam. XXXI. New species of Proctophyllodidae (Sarcoptiformes, Analgoidea). Folia Parasitologica, 21, 349 - 361." type="journal article" year="1974">Černý 1974</bibRefCitation>
; OConnor 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FAF6FCB2695BFCAD" box="[1298,1360,793,818]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">et al.</emphasis>
2005; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FF73FC956D89FCC9" author="Mironov" box="[151,386,829,854]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V., Literak, I. &amp; Capek, M. (2008) New feather mites of the subfamily Pterodectinae (Acari: Astigmata: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) in Mato Grosso do Sul, Brazil. Zootaxa, 1947, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2008">
Mironov 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FEE6FC966D36FCC9" box="[258,317,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
; Valim &amp; Hernandes 2010; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FD23FC95685AFCC9" author="Mironov" box="[711,1105,829,854]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V. &amp; Gonzalez-Acuna, D. (2011) New feather mites of the subfamily Pterodectinae (Astigmata: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) from Chile and Cuba. Zootaxa, 3057, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="2011">Mironov &amp; Gonzalez-Acuña 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FB84FC966890FCC9" author="Gonzalez-Acuna" box="[1120,1179,830,854]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V. &amp; Gonzalez-Acuna, D. A. (2014) Two new species of the feather mite genus Amerodectes Valim et Hernandes, 2010 (Acariformes: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) of the New World. Acarina, 22 (1), 3 - 13." type="journal article" year="2014">2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FB4DFC956CD8FCE5" author="Mironov" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V. &amp; OConnor, B. M. (2014) New species of the feather mite family Proctophyllodidae (Acariformes: Astigmata) from two species of mockingbirds (Passeriformes: Mimidae) in Eastern North America. Journal of Medical Entomology, 51, 529 - 546. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1603 / ME 13109" type="journal article" year="2014">Mironov &amp; OConnor 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FF3AFCC96E15FCE5" author="Mironov" box="[222,542,865,890]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V. &amp; Overstreet, R. M. (2015) A new species of the feather mite genus Amerodectes Valim et Hernandes, 2010 (Acariformes: Proctophyllodidae) from Xanthocephalus xanthocephalus (Passeriformes: Icteridae) in Oregon. Acarina, 23 (1), 74 - 80." type="journal article" year="2015">Mironov &amp; Overstreet 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, the genus is certainly much more diverse than currently known. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FF73FC2D6DA9FC01" author="Park" box="[151,418,901,926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Park, C. K. &amp; Atyeo, W. T. (1971 a) A generic revision of the Pterodectinae, a new subfamily of feather mites (Sarcoptiformes: Analgoidea). Bulletin of the University of Nebraska State Museum, 9, 39 - 88." type="journal article" year="1971" yearSuffix="a">Park &amp; Atyeo (1971a)</bibRefCitation>
erected the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FD5DFC2D6F5AFC01" box="[697,849,901,926]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pterodectinae">Pterodectinae</taxonomicName>
and redefined the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FB6CFC2D6900FC01" box="[1160,1291,901,926]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Pterodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FB6CFC2D6900FC01" box="[1160,1291,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Pterodectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 9 described and about 90 undescribed species. Mironov (
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FCE1FC026F10FC5E" box="[773,795,938,961]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FCC6FC01680DFC5D" author="Mironov" box="[802,1030,937,962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V., Literak, I. &amp; Capek, M. (2008) New feather mites of the subfamily Pterodectinae (Acari: Astigmata: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) in Mato Grosso do Sul, Brazil. Zootaxa, 1947, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2008">
Mironov 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FC68FC026FCEFC5D" box="[908,965,937,962]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
) erected two closely related genera, 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FF73FC656DEDFC79" authority="Mironov, 2008" authorityName="Mironov" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,486,973,998]" class="Aves" family="Furnariidae" genus="Tyrannidectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FF73FC656D3FFC79" box="[151,308,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Tyrannidectes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FED9FC656DEDFC79" author="Mironov" box="[317,486,973,998]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V., Literak, I. &amp; Capek, M. (2008) New feather mites of the subfamily Pterodectinae (Acari: Astigmata: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) in Mato Grosso do Sul, Brazil. Zootaxa, 1947, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2008">Mironov, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FDC6FC656F9BFC79" authority="Mironov, 2008" authorityName="Mironov" authorityYear="2008" box="[546,912,973,998]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Metapterodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FDC6FC656ED7FC79" box="[546,732,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Metapterodectes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FD01FC656F9BFC79" author="Mironov" box="[741,912,973,998]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Mironov, S. V., Literak, I. &amp; Capek, M. (2008) New feather mites of the subfamily Pterodectinae (Acari: Astigmata: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) in Mato Grosso do Sul, Brazil. Zootaxa, 1947, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2008">Mironov, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FB9AFC65690AFC79" box="[1150,1281,973,998]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Pterodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FB9AFC65690AFC79" box="[1150,1281,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Pterodectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the absence of trochanteral seta 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FE37FC5A6DE4FB96" box="[467,495,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">sR</emphasis>
III and genual solenidion 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FCEAFC5A6F17FB96" box="[782,796,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">σ</emphasis>
on legs III. Valim &amp; Hernandes (2010) revised the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FF73FBBD6D11FBB1" box="[151,282,1045,1070]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Pterodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FF73FBBD6D11FBB1" box="[151,282,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Pterodectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and erected a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FDB4FBBD681DFBB1" authority="Valim &amp; Hernandes, 2010" authorityName="Valim &amp; Hernandes" authorityYear="2010" box="[592,1046,1045,1070]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Amerodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FDB4FBBD6ED4FBB1" box="[592,735,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Amerodectes</emphasis>
Valim &amp; Hernandes, 2010
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate species with the following features: setae 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FE4BFB926DC0FBCE" box="[431,459,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">sR</emphasis>
III and solenidion 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FD73FB926EAEFBCE" box="[663,677,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">σ</emphasis>
III are present, epimerites I are fused but never form a long sternum, setae 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FF33FBF66CF9FBE9" box="[215,242,1118,1142]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">c2</emphasis>
are situated off the hysteronotal shield, and in female setae 
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FC41FBF56FCAFBE9" box="[933,961,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">h2</emphasis>
are dagger-like (with or without terminal filament). Undetermined species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D7E2F25A254FDDBFB296EC5FB05" box="[575,718,1153,1178]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Amerodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAEF2F25A254FDDBFB296EC5FB05" box="[575,718,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Amerodectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and related pterodectines are often reported in the faunistic literature on bird-associated mites of the Neotropical region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FCA2FB0D6824FB21" author="Roda" box="[838,1071,1189,1214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Roda, S. A. &amp; Farias, A. M. I. (1999) Acaros plumicolas em aves Passeriformes da Zona da Mata Norte de Pernambuco, Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 16, 879 - 886. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81751999000300025" type="journal article" year="1999">Roda &amp; Farias 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B0C2F25A254FBDEFB0E6934FB21" author="Lyra-Neves" box="[1082,1343,1189,1214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" refString="Lyra-Neves, R. M., Isidro-de-Farias, A. M. &amp; Telino-Junior, W. R. (2003) Ecological relationships between feather mites (Acari) and wild birds of Emberizidae (Aves) in a fragment of Atlantic Forest in northeastern Brazil. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 20, 481 - 485. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81752003000300019" type="journal article" year="2003">
